        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-21T01:21:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder if it\u0027s necessary to compact more than just the head. It takes more time to compact the other elements, and if we\u0027re using an SkArenaAlloc, that block is already allocated and won\u0027t go away until the arena itself is destructed anyway. Why not copy only the head and then steal the rest of the blocks? Is the concern fragmentation?\n\nFor my stroke Op I want the head block to hold exactly one item, which would make the concat extremely simple if implemented this way:\n\n  this-\u003epush_back(std::move(other.headItem()));\n  stealHeapBlocks();",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 276,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 276,
        "endChar": 53
      },
      "revId": "ea76b9d96cbeea3f9a3b5564df0de36a5f41ff83",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8d93b536_f2dbe61f",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrTAllocator.h",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 276,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-21T13:48:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027re right, there\u0027s not much point in compacting extra blocks if everything is already backed on top of an arena. I had been worried about not being able to fill up any dangling space at the old tail block, but I think it\u0027s reasonable to start with just compacting the head block.\n\nThe code was simpler too without the for loop, although I still have it written to handle a variable number of starting items from the template, and to use a bulk memcpy if possible. But when the template arg is 1, like in your case, the concat should basically reduce to a single push_back() + steal.",
      "parentUuid": "5760922d_6aa36e43",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 276,
        "startChar": 7,
